Sure, here are some example sentences that use the Serbian word "postojala" in different forms and positions, along with their English translations:

1. Postojala *je* velika ljubav između njih. (*There was* a great love between them.)
2. Kada *bi postojala* mogućnost za putovanje kroz vrijeme, kamo biste krenuli? (If *there was* a possibility for time travel, where would you go?)
3. Koliko dugo *je postojala* ta firma prije nego što su je ugasili? (How long *did the company exist* before they shut it down?)
4. Mnogo puta sam *postojao* u situaciji sličnoj ovoj. (I have *been* in a situation similar to this many times.)
5. Da li ti misliš da *će postojati* način da se to riješi? (Do you think *there will be* a way to solve that?)
6. Nekada davno, kada *su postojale* stvari poput kazeta i VHS-a, ljudi su morali da paze kako rukuju sa medijima. (Long ago, when *things like* cassettes and VHS tapes *existed*, people had to be careful how they handled the media.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "postojati" means "to exist," and it can be conjugated in different tenses and forms depending on the context. In the examples above, I used different forms of the word to demonstrate its versatility in different sentence structures.